Reviews.Title: QS120F
Reviews.Author: William W. Marsh Jr. "William Marsh"
Reviews.Content: I have a Q-See QSOCWC camera that came with a 60' cable but needed to extend the length.  After adding the 120' extension I got nothing from the camera but white lines and total blanking of the video and no audio.  After using just the 120' cable I got the same thing.

Reviews.Title: it does the job
Reviews.Author: hacks illumine
Reviews.Content: It's thin so it's easy to work with. But I'd keep it away from RFI sources. RFI and EMI easily penetrate the thin sheath causing interference. I'm running this through the plenum ceiling and it works great.May 2, 2011 - I found a better cable like this in black on Amazon. Better insulation, a little thicker, better shielded and cheaper. Far better signal quality than this one, but it's also stiffer. See my other reviews for the exact item.

Reviews.Title: Only works when I *don't* connect the power.
Reviews.Author: S. McMillan
Reviews.Content: Not sure what to say.  I can only use the video and audio cables.  When I connect the power, I get no signal on the other end.  The power cable either has too much loss or creates too much noise.  Either way, its not useful for both power and video.I brought the power up with other means to the camera and it works fine as a carrier for video/audio.  Just not together.

Reviews.Title: Cheapie cable, but it works.  Can't beat the $.
Reviews.Author: ajchin331
Reviews.Content: It works.  This isn't really high-end cable (go figure by the price), but you don't need to buy Monster cable to run a security camera.  Just don't yank on the cable when fishing it into an attic space or the wall.  You'll tear a cable.

Reviews.Title: 120 Ft Extension Cable
Reviews.Author: Cathy L. Hicks
Reviews.Content: Perfect for the use that we needed it for.  Well made.  Connected right up to our video equipment.  Good product.

Reviews.Title: Good value for money
Reviews.Author: Steve C
Reviews.Content: I wanted to project images from my FIOS box to my LCD projector that is in another room located a good 50 feet away. This cable did the job!

Reviews.Title: This cable works great
Reviews.Author: ITAndyB
Reviews.Content: I have been using this cable to extend one of my CCTV cameras in the office for about a month now.  No problems what so ever with connetivity or audio video clarity.

Reviews.Title: For the price, very good results.
Reviews.Author: Rick
Reviews.Content: For the price this cable was more than adaquate for my color cctv. Before this I was using the cable that came with the camera. There were some many harmonic lines on the screen it was completely unexceptable. I took it down cut it up and threw it away. I just installed it and am very pleased. Rick Obenour. Rick's Computer San Diego CA.

Reviews.Title: great cable
Reviews.Author: Four Seasons Yard Care "ghost trackers"
Reviews.Content: i got these cables to hook up to my cameras i use for ghost hunting they are great the power and everything works great i will be getting more of them thanks for a great product  ken  ghost trackers

Reviews.Title: Works - good value.
Reviews.Author: W. Kaye
Reviews.Content: Gee, guess if it works and costs less than other alternatives what more can one ask of a cable bundle...
